==English==
===Etymology===
Perhaps from being first made by Ruby Neenish in the Australian town of [[w:Grong Grong, New South Wales|Grong Grong]] circa 1913.  Or perhaps of German or Vienese origin as "Nienich".  (Reference: Australian National University OzWords October 1995 [http://www.anu.edu.au/andc/ozwords/October_96/5._aussie_words.htm].)
===Noun===
'''neenish [[tart]]'''
# A small tart with a pastry base, cream filling, and covered with icing in two colours, half and half.
